@startuml
title Viaverse Notification / Inbox / Push / Email / SMS — Use Case Diagram
left to right direction

actor User
actor "Admin / Ops" as Admin
actor "Domain Services" as Domain
actor "Push Provider\nFCM/APNs" as Push
actor "SMS / Email Provider\nNetgsm / SMTP" as SmsEmail

rectangle "Notification Boundary" {
  usecase "Consume domain event" as Event
  usecase "Evaluate notification policy" as Policy
  usecase "Apply user preferences\nchannel + quiet hours" as Pref
  usecase "Render localized template" as Template
  usecase "Create in-app inbox item" as Inbox
  usecase "Send push notification" as PushSend
  usecase "Send email" as Email
  usecase "Send SMS / OTP-related alert" as SMS
  usecase "Read notification" as Read
  usecase "Mark as read / archive" as Mark
  usecase "Create digest / summary" as Digest
  usecase "Retry failed delivery" as Retry
  usecase "Admin broadcast\nsegmented + rate limited" as Broadcast
  usecase "Audit campaign/send result" as Audit
  usecase "Emit delivery events\nNotificationSent / Failed" as Events
}

Domain --> Event
Event --> Policy
Policy --> Pref
Pref --> Template
Template --> Inbox
Template --> PushSend
Template --> Email
Template --> SMS
User --> Read
Read --> Mark
Policy ..> Digest : low priority
PushSend ..> Retry : failure
Email ..> Retry : failure
SMS --> Retry : failure
Admin --> Broadcast
Broadcast --> Audit
Retry --> Events
Audit --> Events
Push --> PushSend
SmsEmail --> SMS
SmsEmail --> Email

note bottom
In-app notification is the source user-visible log.
Push/email/SMS are delivery channels with preference,
consent, rate limit and retry policies.
end note
@enduml
